Here is a flowchart definition in Graphviz DOT language based on the description:
```
digraph metabolic_processes {
  node[style=filled];
  edge[arrowsize=0.5];

  start[label="Start", shape= diamond, fillcolor="#6495ED", color="#6495ED"];
  step1[label="Digestion", shape=box, fillcolor="#ADD8E6", color="#ADD8E6"];
  step2[label="Absorption", shape=box, fillcolor="#ADD8E6", color="#ADD8E6"];
  step3[label="Glucose Synthesis", shape=box, fillcolor="#ADD8E6", color="#ADD8E6"];
  step4[label="Fatty Acid Synthesis", shape=box, fillcolor="#ADD8E6", color="#ADD8E6"];
  step5[label="Protein Synthesis", shape=box, fillcolor="#ADD8E6", color="#ADD8E6"];
  decision1[label="Is Energy Needed?", shape=diamond, fillcolor="#FFC080", color="#FFC080"];
  decision2[label="Is Macronutrient Needed?", shape=diamond, fillcolor="#FFC080", color="#FFC080"];
  end[label="End", shape=diamond, fillcolor="#6495ED", color="#6495ED"];

  start -> step1 [label="Digest Nutrients"];
  step1 -> step2 [label="Absorb Nutrients"];
  step2 -> step3 [label=" Synthesize Glucose"];
  step2 -> step4 [label="Synthesize Fatty Acids"];
  step2 -> step5 [label="Synthesize Protein"];
  step3 -> decision1 [label="Provision Energy"];
  step4 -> decision2 [label="Provide Energy"];
  step5 -> decision2 [label="Provide Energy"];
  decision1 -> (start)[label="Yes"] [dir=back];
  decision1 -> end [label="No"] [dir=back];
  decision2 -> (start)[label="Macronutrient Required"] [dir=back];
  decision2 -> end [label="No Macronutrient Required"] [dir=back];
}
```
This flowchart represents the major steps of metabolic processes in the human body. The nodes are labeled with descriptive text, and the edges represent the flow of nutrients and energy through the metabolic pathways. The nodes are styled with colorful fills and shapes, with diamond-shaped nodes indicating decision points (Questions asked) and box-shaped nodes representing process steps.
